Create a new empty report definition file.

Font

data.value:
Font Size
Change the font size of the currently selected field or fields.

data.name: rbtnFontSizeUp.ToolTip
data.value:
Increase Font Size
Increase the font size of the currently selected field or fields by 1pt.

data.name: rbtnFontSizeDown.ToolTip
data.value:
Decrease Font Size

data.name: rbtnFontBold.ToolTip
data.value:
Bold (Ctrl+B)
Make the font of the currently selected field(s) bold.

data.name: rbtnFontItalic.ToolTip
data.value:
Italic (Ctrl+I)
Make the font of the currently selected field(s) italic.

data.name: rbtnFontUnderline.ToolTip
data.value:
Underline (Ctrl+U)
Make the font of the currently selected field(s) underlined.

data.name: rbtnTextAlignGeneral.ToolTip
data.value:
Align General
Align numbers to the right, other values to the left.

data.name: rbtnTextAlignLeft.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Text Left
Align text in the currently selected field(s) with the left bound.

data.name: rbtnTextAlignCenter.ToolTip
data.value:
Center Text
Center text in the currently selected field(s) between the left and right bounds.

data.name: rbtnTextAlignRight.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Text Right
Align text in the currently selected field(s) with the right bound.

data.name: rbtnTextAlignJustify.ToolTip
data.value:
Justify Text
Distribute text evenly between the field's left and right bounds.

data.name: rbtnTextColor.ToolTip
data.value:
Font Color

data.name: rbtnFillColor.ToolTip
data.value:
Fill Color
Change the background color of the currently selected field(s).

data.name: rgalBorderStyle.ToolTip
data.value:
Border Line Style
The style of the border lines of the currently selected field or fields.
If a field has a line slant specified, the style applies to the line.

data.name: rclrBorderColor.ToolTip
data.value:
Border Line Color
The color of border lines of the currently selected field or fields..

data.name: rcmbBorderWidth.ToolTip
data.value:
Border Line Width
The thickness of border lines of the currently selected field or fields, in twips.

(One twip is 1/440 of an inch, or 1/20 of a point.)

data.name: rbtnStyles.ToolTip
data.value:
Report Styles
Apply one of the predefined report styles to the current report.

(Those are the same styles which are available when creating a new report.)

data.name: rbtnApplyStyleToSelection.ToolTip
data.value:
Format Painter

To apply formatting of one field to several other fields:

  1. Click on the field with formatting that you want to apply to other fields. This field becomes the primary selection (indicated by hollow selection handles).
  2. Ctrl+Click to select the fields which you want to format like the primary selected field (the secondary selection is indicated by solid selection handles).
  3. Click this button to copy formatting from the first selected field (primary selection) to the whole selection.

data.name: rbtnFormatAsTableRow.ToolTip
data.value:
As Table Row
Arrange the selected fields into a single table-like row across the report, with the same height and solid borders.
The last selected field's vertical position and height are used as the row's position and height.

Note: the last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields (if any) are drawn with hollow selection handles.
Ctrl+click a field twice to make it the last selected.

rbtnDataSources.ToolTip
data.value:
Data Sources

Edit, add or remove data sources.

Click this button to edit the report's main data source (if currently there is no main data source, you will be prompted to add one).

All report data sources appear in the dropdown, where you can set a data source as main, edit or remove it, or add a new one.

data.name: rbtnGroupSort.ToolTip
data.value:
Groups
Add, remove or edit groups.

data.name: rbtnReportInfo.ToolTip
data.value:
Report Info

Add or change meta information about the current report, such as title, author, and so on.

Optionally the specified information can be applied to all reports in the current file.

data.name: rbtnScriptEditor.ToolTip
data.value:
VBScript Editor (F7)

Open VBScript Editor where you can edit scripts and expressions associated with various report objects

The following scripts are available:

  • Scripts associated with report events: OnOpen, OnClose, OnNoData, OnPage, OnError;
  • Scripts associated with section events: OnFormat, OnPrint;
  • Calculated fields' expressions (Text property of calculated fields);
  • GlobalScripts where you can define functions and subroutines that can be called from other scripts in the current report.

data.name: rbtnShowPropertyGrid.ToolTip
data.value:
Properties (F4)

Show properties of the currently selected object or objects.

data.name: rbtnShowDataTree.ToolTip
data.value:
Data (Shift+F4)

Show and activate the data tree of the current report.

The data tree shows the report's parameters and data sources, data fields and calculated fields.

data.name: rbtnShowErrorList.ToolTip
data.value:
Error List

Show the list of warnings and errors generated when previewing the report.

(The error list shows automatically when a report generates any warnings or errors.)

data.name: rbmCaptionsVisibility.ToolTip
data.value:
Captions

Choose whether to show section captions, sub-section captions, or neither in the designer panel.

You can also collapse or expand all sections in the report.

data.name: rbtnFieldArrow.ToolTip
data.value:
Arrow (Esc)
Cancel any currently started field insert operation, changing the Cross mouse cursor back to Arrow.

data.name: rbtnFieldDataField.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Text Field

Add a data-bound text field or a static text label.

All available bindable data fields (if any) appear in the dropdown. Click on a field in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add an unbound text label, click the button itself, then drag the mouse to insert the label.

data.name: rbtnFieldRtf.ToolTip
data.value:
Add RTF Field

Add a data-bound RTF field or a static RTF label.

All available bindable data fields (if any) appear in the dropdown. Click on a field in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add an unbound RTF label, click the button itself, then drag the mouse to insert the label.

data.name: rbtnFieldParagraph.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Paragraph Field

Add a paragraph containing multiple formatted fragments of static or data bound text.

data.name: rbtnFieldCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Checkbox

Add a data-bound or static checkbox.

All available bindable data fields (if any) appear in the dropdown. Click on a field in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add an unbound checkbox, click the button itself, then drag the mouse to insert the checkbox.

data.name: rbtnFieldBarCode.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Barcode

Add a data-bound or static barcode.

All available bindable data fields (if any) appear in the dropdown. Click on a field in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add a static barcode, click the button itself, then drag the mouse to insert the barcode.

data.name: rbtnFieldCalculated.ToolTip
data.value:
Add a calculated field

Add a calculated field.

Some commonly used expressions (such as creation date or page counts) appear in the dropdown. Click on a predefined expression in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add an arbitrary formula click the button itself. The script editor dialog will appear. Specify the expression and click OK to close the dialog, then drag the mouse to insert the field with the specified expression.

data.name: rbtnFieldPicture.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Image

Add a data-bound or a static image.

All available bindable image and byte array data fields (if any) appear in the dropdown. Click on a field in the dropdown to select it, then drag the mouse to insert it into the report.

To add a static image click the button itself. The file open dialog will appear. Specify the image file and click OK to close the dialog, then drag the mouse to insert the selected image.

data.name: rbtnFieldShape.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Shape

Click the mouse to mark one corner of the shape bounds, then drag the mouse to position the opposite corner. This inserts a static shape field.

Go to the field's properties to change the shape.

data.name: rbtnFieldSubReport.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Sub-Report

Available reports appear in the dropdown. Click a report to select it, then drag the mouse to insert the sub-report into the current report.

The associated report can be changed via the SubReport property on the field.

data.name: rbtnFieldChart.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Chart

Click the mouse to mark one corner of the chart field, then drag the mouse to position the opposite corner. This inserts a chart field into the report.

Go to the properties window or right-click on the field and select appropriate items from the context menu to adjust the chart properties.

data.name: rbtnFieldFlexChart.ToolTip
data.value:
Add FlexChart

Click the mouse to mark one corner of the chart field, then drag the mouse to position the opposite corner. This inserts a chart field into the report.

Go to the properties window or right-click on the field and select appropriate items from the context menu to adjust the chart properties.

data.name: rbtnFieldLegacy.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Legacy Field

Insert a legacy Field, backwards-compatible with C1Report universal field type.

Various properties on this field type allow it to be used in place of different more specialized field types, but using it is not recommended because it may result in degraded performance and increased memory consumption.

Note that some features may not be available when using this legacy field type.

data.name: rbtnSubSectionAdd.ToolTip
data.value:
Add SubSection
Add a new empty sub-section to the current section of the report.

data.name: rbtnSubSectionRemove.ToolTip
data.value:
Remove SubSection
Remove the current sub-section.
Note that all fields contained in the current sub-section will also be removed.

data.name: rbtnSubSectionMoveUp.ToolTip
data.value:
Move SubSection Up
Move the current sub-section up within the containing section.

data.name: rbtnSubSectionMoveDown.ToolTip
data.value:
Move SubSection Down
Move the current sub-section down within the containing section.

data.name: rbtnSnapToGrid.ToolTip
data.value:
Snap to Grid

Toggle snap to grid mode in the designer on or off.

If snap to grid is on, when moving a field in the designer the field automatically snaps to the nearest grid line. This makes it easier to exactly align several fields.

If snap to grid is off, fields can be moved smoothly to any location.

data.name: rbtnShowGrid.ToolTip
data.value:
Show Grid (Ctrl+G)

Shows or hides the alignment grid on the designer surface.

The grid may be helpful when arranging elements on the designer surface.

The grid's properties can be adjusted on the Design Pane tab of the Options dialog (FILE | Options).

data.name: rbtnLockFields.ToolTip
data.value:
Lock Fields

Lock the fields' location and size so they cannot be accidentally moved in the designer.

This may be useful when you want to adjust some fields' properties (such as fonts or colors) but want to keep the layout exactly as it is.

data.name: rbtnGridProperties.ToolTip
data.value:
Grid Properties
Open the report designer options dialog on the Design Pane page, where you can adjust the properties of the alignment grid such as grid units, spacing and so on.

data.name: rbtnAlignLeft.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Left

Align the selected fields to the left bound of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnAlignRight.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Right

Align the selected fields to the right bound of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnAlignCenter.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Center

Center the selected fields between the left and right bounds of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnAlignTop.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Top

Align the selected fields to the top bound of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnAlignBottom.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Bottom

Align the selected fields to the bottom bound of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnAlignMiddle.ToolTip
data.value:
Align Middle

Center the selected fields vertically between the top and bottom bounds of the last selected field.

(The last selected field is drawn with solid selection handles, while other selected fields are drawn with hollow selection handles.

data.name: rbtnEqualHorizontalSpacing.ToolTip

Equalize Horizontal Spacing

data.name: rbtnIncreaseHorizontalSpacing.ToolTip
data.value:
Increase Horizontal Spacing

Equalize and then Increase horizontal spacing between the selected fields.

data.name: rbtnDecreaseHorizontalSpacing.ToolTip
data.value:
Decrease Horizontal Spacing

Equalize and then decrease horizontal spacing between the selected fields.

data.name: rbtnEqualVerticalSpacing.ToolTip
data.value:
Equalize Vertical Spacing

Equalize vertical spacing between the selected fields.

data.name: rbtnIncreaseVerticalSpacing.ToolTip
data.value:
Increase Vertical Spacing

Equalize and then Increase vertical spacing between the selected fields.

data.name: rbtnDecreaseVerticalSpacing.ToolTip
data.value:
Decrease Vertical Spacing

Snap to Grid

data.name: rbtnBringToFront.ToolTip

Bring to Front
Bring the currently selected field(s) to the front of the z-order.

data.name: rbtnSendToBack.ToolTip
data.value:
Send to Back
Send the currently selected field(s) to the back of the z-order.

To Tallest

data.name: rbtnHeightToShortest.ToolTip

To Shortest
Make the heights of all selected fields equal to the height of the shortest field.

To Widest
Make the widths of all selected fields equal to the width of the widest field.

To Narrowest

Size to Grid
